\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Single-shot vs.\ reviewed quality across six modalities, Claude Sonnet 4. Means and standard deviations are computed across three independent on-policy runs (per-run means, then aggregated). Code is binary pass-rate; other modalities are continuous in $[0,1]$. $p$-values: one-sided paired sign test on per-task means. \textbf  {Bold} marks rows where the lift clears $p < 0.05$. Code is scored by execution (\texttt  {pytest}); video by a native full-video rubric (Gemini\nobreakspace  {}3.1\nobreakspace  {}Pro judging the whole rendered clip); the four visual/factual rows use a holistic screenshot judge and serve here as a cross-modal overview, with the precise web and animation figures given by the binary rubric in \Cref  {tab:rubric} and the academic-figure and slide results by deterministic geometry in \Cref  {tab:geometric}.\relax }}{9}{table.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:harness-headline}{{2}{9}{Single-shot vs.\ reviewed quality across six modalities, Claude Sonnet 4. Means and standard deviations are computed across three independent on-policy runs (per-run means, then aggregated). Code is binary pass-rate; other modalities are continuous in $[0,1]$. $p$-values: one-sided paired sign test on per-task means. \textbf {Bold} marks rows where the lift clears $p < 0.05$. Code is scored by execution (\texttt {pytest}); video by a native full-video rubric (Gemini~3.1~Pro judging the whole rendered clip); the four visual/factual rows use a holistic screenshot judge and serve here as a cross-modal overview, with the precise web and animation figures given by the binary rubric in \Cref {tab:rubric} and the academic-figure and slide results by deterministic geometry in \Cref {tab:geometric}.\relax }{table.caption.16}{}}
\newlabel{tab:harness-headline@cref}{{[table][2][]2}{[1][8][]9}}
